<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-lazY-P8YHUHMW_6FnrKRAQ" name=",_TAtrwKZ7EeCmPtYkD7g0pw" guid="-lazY-P8YHUHMW_6FnrKRAQ" changeDate="2011-08-24T06:44:50.818-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The assessment of functional safety is initiated by the organizational body responsible for the functional safety of&#xD;
    the item. This could be the vehicle manufacturer or supplier. It is a highly recommended practice for items with an&#xD;
    ASIL B and a requirement for items with an ASIL of C or D.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The functional safety assessment report assesses each of the steps of the safety lifecycle as it appears in ISO 26262,&#xD;
    volume 2, figure 2. It is from this that the specific topics to be addressed by the functional safety assessment are&#xD;
    identified.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The functional safety assessment will be carried out in accordance with ISO 26262, volume 2, clause 6.4.6. based upon the&#xD;
    measures in&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/tasks/Determine%20confirmation%20measures_101A6AFA.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_04W6sIh2EeCE4bK4CwiExg&quot;>Determine confirmation measures&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To asses how well the development process for the item, through the Safety Lifecycle, has been carried out.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
